      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Race for No. 2: A Debate With a Difference</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carrie Spiros letter, commenting on October 6 article, lauds vice presidential debate between Democratic candidate Sen Jospeh I Lieberman and Republican rival Dick Cheney; says both should be proud</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a twentysomething voter in a voting bloc that neither party has managed to motivate, I think that Thursday night's vice-presidential debate was an important one for the American people, especially young voters (front page, Oct. 6).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a twentysomething voter in a voting bloc that neither party has managed to motivate, I think that Thursday night's vice-presidential debate was an important one for the American people, especially young voters (front page, Oct. 6).</p>
        <p>Many of us were aching for a chance to remember why many love politics and want to put faith in the system.</p>
        <p>Dick Cheney and Joseph I. Lieberman should be proud, and the principals on their respective tickets should take a good hard look at what they did not do last Tuesday and change it for the next debate.</p>
        <p>CARRIE SPIROS  Danvers, Mass., Oct. 6, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
